definitions: (of a number of things) put or arranged in a stack or stacks
shortDefinitions: put or arranged in stack or stacks

definitions: (of a place or surface) filled or covered with goods
(of a machine) having sections that are arranged vertically

examples.text: full-sized washer-dryers are replacing stacked units

shortDefinitions: having sections that are arranged vertically

definitions: (of a heel) made from thin layers of wood, plastic, or another material glued one on top of the other

examples.text: the new boots you buy will be leather with stacked heels

shortDefinitions: made from thin layers of material glued one on top of other

definitions: (of a deck of cards) shuffled or arranged dishonestly so as to gain an unfair advantage

examples.text: you were playing against a stacked deck
a stacked deck of a political system

shortDefinitions: (of pack of cards) shuffled or arranged dishonestly so as to gain unfair advantage

definitions: (of a task) placed in a queue for subsequent processing

examples.text: an operating system that allows for stacked jobs

shortDefinitions: (of task) placed in queue for subsequent processing

definitions: (of a stream of data) stored in such a way that the most recently stored item is the first to be retrieved

examples.text: MIDI interface featuring stacked MIDI note numbers

shortDefinitions: (of stream of data) stored in such way that most recently stored item is first to be retrieved
